enhanced_by.reason: The empty() method can be used to initialize an empty FluentIterable before calling of() to ensure a valid state.
The toList() method can be used to prepare a list of elements that can be passed to the of() method for conversion into a FluentIterable.
The size() method can be used to verify the number of elements in the FluentIterable created by the of() method.
The isEmpty() method can be used to verify if the FluentIterable created by the of() method is empty.
The contains(Object) method can be used to verify if a specific element is present in the FluentIterable created by the of() method.
